  "chapter": {
    "number": 21,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job: God Will Punish the Wicked"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Job answered:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Listen carefully to my words;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let this be your consolation to me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bear with me while I speak;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then, after I have spoken, you may go on mocking.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is my complaint against a man?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Then why should I not be impatient?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Look at me and be appalled;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "put your hand over your mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I remember, terror takes hold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my body trembles in horror.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do the wicked live on,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "growing old and increasing in power?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their descendants are established around them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their offspring before their eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their homes are safe from fear;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no rod of punishment from God is upon them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their bulls breed without fail;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their cows bear calves and do not miscarry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They send forth their little ones like a flock;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their children skip about,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "singing to the tambourine and lyre",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and making merry at the sound of the flute.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They spend their days in prosperity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and go down to Sheol in peace.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3177
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet they say to God: ‘Leave us alone!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For we have no desire to know Your ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who is the Almighty, that we should serve Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and what would we gain if we pray to Him?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Still, their prosperity is not in their own hands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so I stay far from the counsel of the wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How often is the lamp of the wicked put out?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does disaster come upon them?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Does God, in His anger, apportion destruction?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Are they like straw before the wind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like chaff swept away by a storm?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is said that God lays up one’s punishment for his children.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let God repay the man himself, so he will know it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let his eyes see his own destruction;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let him drink for himself the wrath of the Almighty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For what does he care about his household after him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the number of his months has run out?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can anyone teach knowledge to God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "since He judges those on high?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One man dies full of vigor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "completely secure and at ease.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His body is well nourished,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3178
          },
          {
            "text": "and his bones are rich with marrow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet another man dies in the bitterness of his soul,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "having never tasted prosperity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But together they lie down in the dust,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and worms cover them both.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I know your thoughts full well,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the schemes by which you would wrong me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you say, ‘Where now is the nobleman’s house,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and where are the tents in which the wicked dwell?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have you never asked those who travel the roads?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Do you not accept their reports?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, the evil man is spared from the day of calamity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "delivered from the day of wrath.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who denounces his behavior to his face?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who repays him for what he has done?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is carried to the grave,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and watch is kept over his tomb.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The clods of the valley are sweet to him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "everyone follows behind him,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and those before him are without number.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So how can you comfort me with empty words?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For your answers remain full of falsehood.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
